abstract: In the following list "mtg" stands for mortgage and "R S" for revenue stamps. The war revenue law provides that stamps shall be placed on all conveyances at the rate of 50 cents for each $500 of consideration. This "consideration" has been held to mean only the equity above the mortgage. The amount of the mortgage plus 1,000 times the value of the revenue stamps on the conveyances should therefore show the true consideration.

abstract: In the following list "mtg" stands for mortgage and "R S" for revenue stamps. The war revenue law provides that stamps shall be placed on all conveyances at the rate of 50 cents for each $500 of consideration. abstract: NEWPORT, R.I., Sept. 7. -- P.F. Collier introduced the most original entertainment of the season this evening in the shape of a jungle party. abstract: LONDON, Sept. 8. -- The Chinese crisis presents no new feature this morning. Nothing appears to be certain. abstract: GREENWICH, Conn., Sept. 8. -- Belle Haven-on-the-Sound marked the close of its Summer season this afternoon by holding its tenth annual horse show in front of the Casino. abstract: From The Atlantic. Yesterday Nature bore herself proudly; now she appears overwhelmed and tearful. The plumed bamboos which held themselves so haughtily are now spread and bent under the incessant beat of the rain, and cataracts run through their battered leaves. The fields have turned to lakes, the streams are rivers, the rivers are floods; and these roofs of bamboo and nipa are irrigating pipes guiding numberless Jets inside the houses.

abstract: In the following list "mtg" stands for mortgage and "R S" for revenue stamps. The war revenue law provides that stamps shall be placed on all conveyances at the rate of 50 cents for each $500 of consideration. This "consideration" has been held to mean only the equity above the mortgage. The amount of the mortgage plus 1,000 times the value of the revenue stamps on the conveyances should therefore show the true consideration.

abstract: In the following list "mtg" stands for mortgage and "R S" for revenue stamps. The war revenue law provides that stamps shall be placed on all conveyances at the rate of 5O cents for each $500 of consideration. The amount of the mortgage plus 1,000 times the value of the revenue stamps on the conveyances should therefore show the true consideration.

abstract: In the following list "mtg" stands for mortgage and "R S" for revenue stamps. The war revenue law provides that stamps shall be placed on all conveyances at the rate of 50 cents for each $500 of consideration. This "consideration " has been held to mean only the equity above the mortgage. The amount of the mortgage plus 1.000 times the value of the revenue stamps on the conveyances should therefore show the true consideration.

abstract: HAZLETON, Penn., Sept. 12 -- The news of the declaration of the big coal strike was received in Hazleton to-night. It traveled quickly, and crowds of people soon gathered on the streets. abstract: In the following list "mtg" stands for mortgage and "RS" for revenue stamps. The war revenue law provides that stamps shall be placed on all conveyances at the rate of 50 cents for each $500 of consideration. The amount of the mortgage plus 1,000 times the value of the revenue stamps on the conveyances should therefore show the true consideration.

abstract: In the following list "mtg" stands for mortgage and "R S" for revenue stamps. The war revenue law provides that stamps shall be placed on all conveyances at the rate of 50 cents for each $500 of consideration. This "consideration" has been held to mean only the equity above the mortgage. The amount of the mortgage plus 1,000 times the value of the revenue stamps on the conveyances should therefore show the true consideration.

abstract: From The Fortnightly Review. The growing costliness of fashionable London tends to exclude from its most modish circles a class that could perhaps ill be spared. That phenomenon, however, is not peculiar to the capital. It is to be found in all parts of the provinces: it is but one of the many indications of the changes inseparable from the substitution of commerce for land as a foundation of national prosperity.

Orders were issued at the coal company offices to-night to the effect that all collieries would be operated on full time next week. If not enough men report, then work will be shut down altogether until the strike is settled.

abstract: In the following list "mtg" stands for mortgage and "R S" for revenue stamps. The war revenue law provides that stamps shall be placed on all conveyances at the rate of 50 cents for each $500 of consideration. This "consideration" has been held to mean only the equity above the mortgage. The amount of the mortgage plus 1,000 times the value of the revenue stamps on the conveyances should therefore show the true consideration.

abstract: NEWPORT, R.I., Sept. 17. -- Wounds of various kinds about their favorite hunters sustained in Saturday's very stiff chase prevented several of Newport's most skillful and daring cross-country riders from taking part in to-day's hunt. abstract: PRINCETON, N.J., Sept. 19 -- The formal opening of Princeton University was held in Marquand Chapel this afternoon at 3 o'clock. President Patton, in greeting the students, congratulated the freshman class upon its being the largest that ever entered the university. abstract: After a terrific fight with the Galveston hurricane, the steamship Hyades, badly battered, and with several of her crew injured, reached Dow's Stores, Brooklyn, yesterday. She is the first ship which went through the territle Gulf storm to reach this port. abstract: DALLAS, Texas, Sept. 21. -- The storm of last night over Northern and Northwestern Texas was one of the fiercest rain and electrical affairs of which there is any record. The property loss within a radius of a hundred miles of Dallas is estimated at $2,000,000, confined largely to cotton and railway interests.

abstract: SHENANDOAH, Penn., Sept. 22 -- With the arrival of the militia here to-day this borough assumed its normal condition, and the anticipated resumption of violence on the part of the miners did not occur. It might have been the presence of the soldiers that restrained the turbulent element, but many of the residents believe the lack of riotous scenes was due to the fact that all the collieries here were closed.

Andre, Minister of War, has reported to President Loubet in favor of authorizing Paris and Bazeilles to place the cross of the Legion of Honor in the municipal arms, in recognition of their splendid defense in 1870 against the Germans. abstract: The thirty inhabitants of Whitepot, L.I., were shocked lately to learn that one of their number had been arrested upon his arrival in Germany on suspicion of being an Anarchist detailed to shoot the Kaiser. abstract: PHILADELPHIA, Penn., Sept. 25. -- The University of Pennsylvania's gridiron warriors for the first time this season lined up against one another in actual combat to-day on Franklin Field without a score by either side. abstract: ITHACA, N.Y., Sept. 26. -- Cornell opened the season in football on Percy Field this afternoon, and defeated Colgate by 16 points to nothing. The game was easily won. Although Cornell's team was made up largely of new men, they showed the effects of a week's coaching under Houghton, and rarely had difficulty in graining through the visitors' line or stopping the rushes.

abstract: SAVANNAH, Sept. 27. -- Some time ago the Plant system of railroads made its return for taxation. abstract: In the following list "mtg" stands for mortgage and "R S" for revenue stamps The war revenue law provides that stamps shall be placed on all conveyances at the rate of 50 cents for each $500 of consideration. abstract: We find everywhere that blood is blended into complex ritual customs, and thus associated with complex emotional states. abstract: Until 1820 the fate of Mexico and its inhabitants was the same as Spain has dealt out to all her colonies; they were oppressed, robbed, murdered, and trodden under foot by a long succession of infamous and heartless rulers, whose only creed was their own enrichment, who feared neither God nor man, and whose systematic course of torture and death seems to have been as necessary to them as their daily food.

abstract: POTTSVILLE, Sept. 29 -- The Eastern shipments of bituminous coal are enormous, and to-day the Reading Company sent to Harrisburg a large number of locomotives employed in the coal trade. The Western Maryland Railroad Company has been pouring soft coal into the Reading yard at Shippensburg during the past few days so rapidly that the yard at that point became congested.

abstract: Some improvement shows in Wall Street sentiment. Market values are not advancing, but there are evidences of a material modification of that uneasiness which for months past has been ruling. Especial reasons for this do not clearly appear, though what can be counted effective appears in the non-fulfillment of depressing predictions on account of which the market at various times has been put under pressure.
